## ğŸ“˜ About
**Pahana Edu** is a modular, extensible billing system built with:
- Java (Servlets + JSP), JDBC (HikariCP pool)
- MVC pattern, DAO layer, Factory & Singleton patterns
- RESTful APIs for distributed clients
- MySQL / PostgreSQL support

Designed for production use in educational bookstores â€” multi-role dashboards (Admin, Cashier, StoreKeeper), inventory control, billing, supplier mapping, and reporting.

---

## ğŸ— Architecture (3-Tier + Patterns)

![3-Tier architecture](docs/architecture/3-tier-architecture.png)

**Layers**
1. **Presentation (Client)** â€” JSP + Bootstrap: role-based dashboards, client-side validation & animations.
2. **Application (Tomcat)** â€” Servlets (controllers), Services (business logic), REST endpoints, DAO layer for persistence.
3. **Data (DB)** â€” MySQL/Postgres accessed via JDBC + HikariCP.

**Design patterns**: MVC, DAO, Factory, Singleton, Service Layer.

---

## âœ¨ Highlights & Features
- âœ… Role-based dashboards (Admin, Cashier, StoreKeeper)  
- âœ… Billing with line items, discounts, and history  
- âœ… Inventory: stock counts, low-stock alerts, supplier mapping  
- âœ… REST APIs (JSON) for external clients  
- âœ… Dark/Light UI toggle + animated counters and card hover effects  
- âœ… Connection pooling (HikariCP) + centralized DAOFactory  
- âœ… Sample SQL seed data & migration scripts

